Class FormulaCompilerNoPiecewise

All Implemented Interfaces:
ASTNodeCompiler
public class FormulaCompilerNoPiecewise
extends FormulaCompiler

Produces an infix formula like FormulaCompiler but removes all the piecewise functions. They are replaced by an id that is unique if you are using the same FormulaCompilerNoPiecewise instance. The content of the piecewise function is put in a Map and is transformed to use if/then/else. This class is used for example to create an SBML2XPP converter where (in XPP) the piecewise operator is not supported.
